OL,3,CWales to have more say over Crown
OL,4,CEstate
OL,6,FThis has been a long-running political
OL,7,Frow. The land and seabed areas are
OL,8,Fowned by the monarchy but run by the
OL,9,FCrown Estate for the UK Government
OL,10,Fwith its proceeds going partly to fund
OL,11,Fthe Royal Family and partly to the UK
OL,12,FTreasury.
OL,14,FIn Scotland it's devolved, meaning
OL,15,Fthat the Scottish Government gets the
OL,16,Fproceeds. That's not the case here
OL,17,Falthough three of the political
OL,18,Fparties - Welsh Labour, Plaid Cymru
OL,19,Fand the Welsh Liberal Democrats - have
OL,20,Fcalled for the power to be transferred
OL,21,Fto the Welsh Government.
